      <title outputclass="H4ForH3_1_9" class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">32.503-10</ph> Establishing
alternate liquidation rates.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d2102e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li otherprops="abc" outputclass="H5_abc" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d2116e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  The contracting officer must ensure
that the liquidation rate is-</p>
               <ol id="d2102e23" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2116e27" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        High enough to result in Government
recoupment of the applicable progress payments on each billing;
and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2116e36" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        Supported by documentation included
in the administration office contract file.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="abc" outputclass="H5_abc" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d2116e47" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  The minimum liquidation rate is
the expected progress payments divided by the contract price.Each
of these factors is discussed below:</p>
               <ol id="d2102e53" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2116e57" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        The contracting officer must compute
the expected progress payments by multiplying the estimated cost
of performing the contract by the progress payment rate.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2116e66" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        For purposes of computing the
liquidation rate, the contracting officer may adjust the estimated
cost and the contract price to include the estimated value of any
work authorized but not yet priced and any projected economic adjustments; however,
the contracting officer’s adjustment must not exceed the Government’s
estimate of the price of all authorized work or the funds obligated
for the contract.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2116e75" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        The following are examples of
the computation. Assuming an estimated price of $2,200,000 and total
estimated costs eligible for progress payments of $2,000,000:</p>
                     <ol id="d2102e81" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li otherprops="i_ii_iii" outputclass="H7_i_ii_iii" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d2116e85" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              If the progress
payment rate is 80 percent, the minimum liquidation rate should
be 72.7 percent, computed as follows:</p>
                           <fig frame="all" class="- topic/fig ">
                              <image href="Graphics/32.503-10formula1.jpg"
                                     height="33.000pt"
                                     width="135.000pt"
                                     placement="inline"
                                     class="- topic/image "/>
                           </fig>
                        </li>
                        <li otherprops="i_ii_iii" outputclass="H7_i_ii_iii" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d2116e99" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              If the progress
payment rate is 85 percent, the minimum liquidation rate should
be 77.3 percent, computed as follows:</p>
                           <fig frame="all" class="- topic/fig ">
                              <image href="Graphics/32.503-10formula2.jpg"
                                     height="33.000pt"
                                     width="135.000pt"
                                     placement="inline"
                                     class="- topic/image "/>
                           </fig>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2116e115" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        Minimum liquidation rates will
generally be expressed to tenths of apercent. Decimals between tenths
will be rounded up to the next highest tenth (not necessarily the
nearest tenth), since rounding down would produce a rate below the
minimum rate calculated.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
